 T O T A L   E N E R G Y  ***  (contributions)  ***
 =======================
  

*** Note ***

The requirements to the integration accuracy are somewhat higher than for bond energies.
One can expect an accuracy of roughly (accint-2) decimal places, where accint is the
general integration accuracy parameter.
The Coulomb energy is the sum of the Hartree energy (electron-electron Coulomb interaction)
and the nuclear-electron attraction energy. It includes the correction for the first-order
fit error in the Hartree energy.
The potential energy is the sum of the nuclear repulsion energy, the Coulomb energy,
and the exchange-correlation energy.

